<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-11-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-11-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="953" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d953">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Minister of Foreign Affairs
                                    of Norway</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Christiania</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-11-01"><hi rend="italic">November 1,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Norwegian Government presents heartiest thanks for kind telegram 30
                            October. Hauge ordered to go Washington immediately as chargé
                            d’affaires.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lövland</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>